main event: A sighting occurred on March 8, 1951, at 45.09N 140.47E in the Far East, which was concluded to be a probable balloon and not a UFO.
interesting points: The sighting was reported as a single object following a course of 035 degrees and maneuvering in a southeast direction.
The conclusion states that it was probably a balloon, aircraft, or astronomical object, with insufficient data for evaluation.
The report was from Project Card and indicated that it was not considered a UFO by FEAF (Far East Air Force).
No photographs were included in the report.
